The paper presents machine learning methods for AC Optimal Powerflow, which involves optimizing power generation in a transmission network while respecting physical and engineering constraints. This problem can be formulated as a machine learning problem, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the problem involves predicting constraints and optimizing solutions, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also involves predicting optimal solutions, which suggests that it may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of machine learning methods for optimization also suggests that it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves validating the approaches on benchmark grids, which suggests that it may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
